description.narrative: The sub-national planning and budgeting advocacy for social services for children in support of the integrated early childhood development has been expanded to 25 provinces, moving from previously seven targeted provinces. Two key strategic interventions were rolled out to strengthen capacity of Ministry of Interior in monitoring and evaluation and governance of sub-national administration (SNA), the sub-national planning and budgeting online database and reward recognition mechanism. The sub-national project and budget database is being developed with the view of linking the SNA planning and budget functions into a consolidated monitoring mechanism informing the performance assessment and budget advocacy | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
